## Implementation Plan: Nightly Release Channel

### Design Decisions
- Nightly hosting: rolling GitHub prerelease tagged `nightly`, assets replaced via --clobber
- Version format: `0.x.y-dev.<unix_seconds>` (e.g. `0.12.0-dev.1740393600`)
- npm nightly: no — GitHub-only
- Channel UX: --channel flag on upgrade + "nightly"/"stable" as special positional version
- Install script: --version nightly reuses existing flag, no new flags needed
- Already up to date: skip unless --force, compare version.json against CLI_VERSION
- Specific version + channel: leave persisted channel as-is
- Non-curl → nightly: auto-migrate to standalone binary, warn about existing install
- CI structure: preceding nightly-version job + publish-nightly job in ci.yml

