### CI Workflow Design
The nightly-version job runs only on main pushes (if condition). When skipped on
PRs, downstream jobs still run (skipped != failed in GitHub Actions). The build-binary
matrix checks if nightly-version output is non-empty before injecting the version.
The publish-nightly job runs only after both build-binary and test-e2e succeed on
main. The rolling nightly release is created once and assets replaced on each push
using gh release upload --clobber.

### Nightly Download URL Pattern
getBinaryDownloadUrl("nightly") produces the same URL pattern as stable releases
but with "nightly" as the tag instead of a version string. The existing .gz
download + decompression logic is fully reused.

### Version Comparison for Nightly
Bun.semver.order() handles nightly-to-nightly correctly because the unix timestamp
in -dev.<ts> is a numeric pre-release identifier, compared numerically. Switching
from stable to nightly is always a download (channelChanged = true bypasses the
already-up-to-date check).

### User Flows
  # Fresh nightly install
  curl -fsSL https://cli.sentry.dev/install | bash -s -- --version nightly

  # Switch existing install to nightly
  sentry cli upgrade nightly
  # or: sentry cli upgrade --channel nightly

  # Regular nightly update (channel persisted)
  sentry cli upgrade

  # Force re-download even if up to date
  sentry cli upgrade --force

  # Switch back to stable
  sentry cli upgrade stable
